Se a função readr::read_csv() está retornando o erro abaixo, é muito provável que o arquivo utiliza um encoding diferente de UTF-8

Error in nchar(x, "width") : invalid multibyte string

Para corrigir isso, use readr::locale() para definir o encoding correto.

#tidyverse #rstats

If readr::read_csv() is returning the error below for you, is likely that your archive is not UTF-8 encoded.

Error in nchar(x, "width") : invalid multibyte string

To fix this, use readr::locale() to define the correct encoding of your file.

One of the most important aspects of #dataviz is choosing the right charts. After all, to tell the story right, you need to visualize the data right.

So here are 3 pointers to keep in mind while you chart your #data

#rstats #DataScience #DataFam #Datavisualization

1. Understand what kind of data you're visualising. That's half the job done.
Are you comparing different parameters? Are you showing an increase/decrease over a period of time? Are you showing how your data has been distributed along different categories? 

#rstats #DataFam

3. Keep your charts simple & clear. When you want the story to reach a larger audience, it is important they get your charts without a lot of additional explanation. Your #dataviz serves no purpose if you've to write a 1000-word essay to elucidate it.

#rstats #DataScience
